functionDefinitions.definition:
Represent the exact boundary of a candidate deterministically using an AreaSpec.

AreaSpec fields (v1):
- areaId: stable slug for the run (derive from candidateType + displayName + stateCodes; keep consistent)
- displayName: human-friendly
- candidateType: metro|city|county|custom
- region: freeform (e.g., "New England", "Mid-Atlantic", "Southeast")
- stateCodes: string[] (required)

Boundary definition (by candidateType):
- metro: { metroName: string, states: string[], definitionSource: string }
- city: { cityName: string, stateCode: string }
- county: { countyName: string, stateCode: string, fips?: string }
- custom (v1 mode): { mode: "radius", center: { place: string, stateCode: string }, radiusMiles: number }

Rule: No candidate may enter candidatePool without an AreaSpec.
